{
  "stem": "27340.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And after two years, believe it or not, they went through the various records, personal records of people as a routine activity, and found that my nationality was German.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was, of course, impossible as far as they were concerned because they considered me to be a hell of a security risk after I'd been with them for two years.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And what sort of security problems one could arrange as a cadet who meets various evenings during the week and the weekends, I fail to see.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But nevertheless, the law is the law.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so, regretfully, they had to dismiss me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "At that time I was studying at evening classes in order to gain my matric so as to ultimately gain entry into university.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And my English teacher, who oddly enough was a Scotsman, heard about this over a cup of tea.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I told him I was depressed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I was expelled or released or dismissed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I was dismissed from the Air Training Corps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he said, oh, man, you want to come and join our mob, the Home Guard.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He was a captain in the Home Guard.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And that, of course, I accepted with open arms, and so I joined the Home Guard.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "The irony of it all was that he introduced me to the commander of the local Home Guard battalion in Walsall.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It was about 2,000 men strong and had, in fact, a number of anti-aircraft batteries that were manned partially by regular forces, mainly women, and partially by Home Guard members, who were part-time soldiers.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They had a proper job during the day like I did, for instance, as a tool maker or apprentice tool maker, and weekends and free time, we were soldiers in the defense of the realm.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
